Get-BinaryType logic:
  - Read file bytes; parse PE optional header to get SizeOfImage
  - Actual PE end = file offset of PE header + PE header size + SizeOfImage (approximate)
  - Better: use IMAGE_OPTIONAL_HEADER SizeOfHeaders + sum of section raw sizes
  - Simplest reliable approach: find end of PE sections via section table
  - Check magic bytes after PE end for ZIP/RAR/7z/GZIP/appended PE
  - Check PE version info strings for SFX keywords
  - Check NSIS markers

What could break:
  - Corrupt/non-PE files — caught by try/catch, IsSFX=false
  - WinRM/WMI: importing Output.psm1 from executor module context — use $PSScriptRoot

Verify: run T09 test suite after each change.

